  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "info_610102": "WHODAS 2.0This questionnaire asks about difficulties due to health conditions. Health conditions include diseases or illnesses, other health problems that may be short or long lasting, injuries, mental or emotional problems, and problems with alcohol or drugs.Think back over the past 30 days and answer these questions, thinking about how much difficulty you had doing the following activities. For each question, please select only one response.",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods": "Standing for long periods such as 30 minutes?",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_standing_long_periods_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities": "Taking care of your household responsibilities?",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_household_responsibilities_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_learning_new_task": "Learning a new task, for example, learning how to get to a new place?",
      "impairment_learning_new_task_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_learning_new_task_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_learning_new_task_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_learning_new_task_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_learning_new_task_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities": "How much of a problem did you have joining in community activities (for example, festivities, religious, or other activities) in the same way as anyone else can?",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_joining_community_activities_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected": "How much have you been emotionally affected by your health problems?",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_emotionally_affected_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes": "Concentrating on doing something for ten minutes?",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_concentrating_ten_minutes_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances": "Walking a long distance such as a kilometer [or equivalent]?",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_walking_long_distances_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_washing_self": "Washing your whole body?",
      "impairment_washing_self_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_washing_self_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_washing_self_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_washing_self_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_washing_self_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_getting_dressed": "Getting dressed?",
      "impairment_getting_dressed_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_getting_dressed_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_getting_dressed_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_getting_dressed_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_getting_dressed_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people": "Dealing with people you do not know?",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_dealing_new_people_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship": "Maintaining a friendship?",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_maintaining_friendship_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_work": "Your day-to-day work?",
      "impairment_work_opt_1": "None",
      "impairment_work_opt_2": "Mild",
      "impairment_work_opt_3": "Moderate",
      "impairment_work_opt_4": "Severe",
      "impairment_work_opt_5": "Extreme or cannot do",
      "impairment_difficult_days_past_month": "Overall, in the past 30 days, how many days were these difficulties present?",
      "impairment_unable_days_past_month": "In the past 30 days, for how many days were you totally unable to carry out your usual activities or work because of any health condition?",
      "impairment_reduced_days_past_month": "In the past 30 days, not counting the days that you were totally unable, for how many days did you cut back or reduce your usual activities or work because of any health condition?",
      "scoring_610102": "Scoring:There are two basic options for computing the summary scores for the WHODAS 2.0 short version.Simple:The scores assigned to each of the items-\"none\" (1), \"mild\" (2) \"moderate\" (3), \"severe\" (4) and \"extreme\" (5) -are summed. This method is referred to as simple scoring because the scores from each of the items are simply added up without recoding or collapsing of response categories; thus, there is no weighting of individual items. This approach is practical to use as a hand-scoring approach and may be the method of choice in busy clinical settings or in paper-pencil interview situations. As a result, the simple sum of the scores of the items across all domains constitutes a statistic that is sufficient to describe the degree of functional limitations.Complex:The more complex method of scoring is called \"item-response-theory\" (IRT)-based scoring. It takes into account multiple levels of difficulty for each WHODAS 2.0 item. It takes the coding for each item response as \"none,\" \"mild,\" \"moderate,\" \"severe,\" and \"extreme\" separately and then uses an algorithm to determine the summary score by differentially weighting the items and the levels of severity. The SPSS algorithm is available from WHO. The scoring has three steps:� Step 1 - Summing of recoded item scores within each domain.� Step 2 - Summing of all six domain scores.� Step 3 - Converting the summary score into a metric ranging from 0 to 100 (where 0 = no disability; 100 = full disability)."
    }
  }
}